{
  "stem": "25348.2",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] And he asked me, how come you're here?",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I lied.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They took us by mistake.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You ask me how was Richard there-- Richard, Dr.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Richard Ludwig.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The German crew-- I only got close to one-- the shooting battalion, they were dead drunk.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I was-- one was so drunk that he lay, prostrate, on the ground.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So Richard-- it must've been providence that he came just at that moment, when we were just holding, in our hand, the bit of our false papers, identifying us as Catholics, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] when he told the Germans he would pledge, he would vouch for these Catholics.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My mother, while we were in the ghetto, she procured the false papers through some Polish bureaucrat, working in a German office.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They had a stamp on.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They had our names on.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they had-- gave the religions, the religion as Catholic.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My name was Caroline Ryjkowska.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I'll spell the surname for you, R-Y-J-K-O-W-S-K-A.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And the test for Germans-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] the test applied by Germans to Poles suspected to be Jews was to make them, to make them pray and to chant their Polish prayers.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] I told you I grew up in a Catholic school, and I knew it inside out.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "My mother came from a religious home.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "She spoke very good Polish, but the doctor lightly kicked her and said, try and faint.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And she gave an Oscar performance that she was fatigued [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] and the, [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] the man, man who gathered himself from the ground said to us, [NON ENGLISH], get out-- get the hell out of here.",
      "word_count": 42
    }
  ],
